 items, both the bard tambourine (six coins, many of which are foraged, some of which are critter drops, all of which are tradable) and the shackle of bronze (all nodrops are foraged, many of the pieces are foraged, the pieces that are critter drops are tradable so can be gotten from other folks) become possible and have good rewards. Likewise the gem inlaid gauntlets which require scrolls that drop from gnolls (which are all tradable, so you don't actually have to kill a thing).<br><br>The runners ring(?) quest is just racing from zone to zone and checking in (talking to) certain NPCs. The value of the quest is negligable, from what I remember, but the item might tie into some higher quest I haven't found or heard of.<br><br>The trick to most of these: You could, easily, repeat the same quest over and over again. Anything with a non-trivial award is going to require SOMETHING beyond a time investment (running to and fro, etc) just to keep you from recycling the quest again and again for salable items, xp, or coinage. So anything that doesn't require risk in the form of combat, dangerous zones, special faction requirements, etc, is going to tend to be trivial in reward even if the time required is so high as to be laughable for normal people.<br><br>Sutekh<br>Twilight Requiem <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/udemorgoth.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Demorgoth</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/10/02 9:59:42 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm13.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=4047.topic&index=20>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> No-killing quests</span><hr size=1> Any quest that requires no killing could potentially be done at L1. For that reason, items from no-killing quests will usually be tailored so as to not be over